div.div:
we now have several components we are going to handle, it makes the issue looks more complicated.
But don't worry about it, anyway, we are still working on a very simple rectangle, not circle, triangle, etc, right :) ? Rectangles already meet at least 95% requirements of all text editing, when we want to develop a text editor, I believe.
The next good news is, we are still working on a TUI editor, not a GUI editor, i.e. in our scenario, a basic rendering unit is a character, a grapheme on the terminal, not a pixel on a 4K-monitor. It reduces the problem scale from millions to thousands! Whew, a long breath.
